      "seed": 418449339,
      "version": 638,
      "versionNonce": 1818372912,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1773170904295,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What are some reasons\nyou might have multiple processes\nin the same app?\n\n- \"Part of the same bounded context\"\n    - same resources / etc.\n\n\n- Improving the design of existing services\n    - monolith to microservices\n    - create small services for new stuff\n        - don't double down on bad arch,\n    - pick low hanging fruit and move it into\n       other services at your own pace.\n\n- Scaling out using the process model.\n\n\n- Splitting stuff up for work / brains / testing etc.\n\n- Late binding is resolving temporal coupling.\n    - service b changes at a different rate than a.\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What are some reasons\nyou might have multiple processes\nin the same app?\n\n- \"Part of the same bounded context\"\n    - same resources / etc.\n\n\n- Improving the design of existing services\n    - monolith to microservices\n    - create small services for new stuff\n        - don't double down on bad arch,\n    - pick low hanging fruit and move it into\n       other services at your own pace.\n\n- Scaling out using the process model.\n\n\n- Splitting stuff up for work / brains / testing etc.\n\n- Late binding is resolving temporal coupling.\n    - service b changes at a different rate than a.\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
